CERN Open Hardware Licence Version 2 - Strongly Reciprocal

Preamble

CERN has developed this licence to promote collaboration among hardware
engineers and to provide a legal tool which supports the freedom to use,
study, modify, share and distribute hardware designs and products based on
those designs. This licence is derived from the Open SourceInitiative (OSI)
approved CERN Open Hardware Licence - Permissive and complies with the
Open Source Definition. It was created for users of hardware designs who
require that all downstream modifications are shared in the same way.

You are free to:

- use this work for any purpose,
- study how it works,
- modify it,
- share it with others,
- share modifications with others.

Under these conditions:

- You must provide - without charge - all source files, documentation, and
circuit board designs for any hardware you create or manufacture based on
this work to anyone who asks.

- You must provide under the same licence anything you create that
incorporates or is derived from this work, whether modified or not.

- You must ensure that recipients are aware of these conditions.

Full licence text: https://ohwr.org/cern_ohl_s_v2.txt

This is a summary of the licence terms. The full legal text is available
at the link above.